w:r.w:t: Prohibition on Discrimination and Preferential Treatment by Colorado Governments
Prohibition on Certain Conditions of Employment
– Eliminates Unions for public sector employees.
– Increases the betting limit at Casinos.
State Sales Tax for Services for Individuals with Developmental Disabilities
– Additional tax provides earmarked funding for the disabled.
– Taxes earmarked for I-70 transportation needs.
Liability of Business Entities and Their Executive Officials
– Criminalizes any errors made by management.
Restrictions on Campaign Contributions from Government Sole-Source Contractors
– Eliminates contributions from public sector unions and some companies.
Just Cause for Employee Discharge or Suspension
– Makes it virtually impossible to fire any employee.
– Forces company healthcare insurance, will drive some companies out of business.
– Places vague unknown workplace requirements on companies.
– Eliminates Oil company credit, funds College scholarships for Colorado residents.
– Provides long-term funding for K-12 schools.
Age Qualification for Serving in General Assembly
– Can run for office at age 21.
Elimination of Obsolete Constitutional Provisions Regarding Land Value Increase
Elimination of Obsolete Constitutional Provisions Regarding Intoxicating Liquors
– Makes it easier to put state statue initiatives on the ballot, harder to put proposed amendments on.
